Never Have I Ever Privacy Policy
1. Introduction
Welcome to Never Have I Ever. We prioritize your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines our practices regarding data collection, use, and disclosure in relation to your use of Never Have I Ever.
2. Consent and User Control
By downloading and using Never Have I Ever, you consent to the practices outlined in this Privacy Policy. Depending on your region and device operating system, you may have the option to further configure your consent preferences within our app, including settings related to data collection for analytics and advertisements.
3. Data Collection and Use
While we ourselves do not collect or store personal data, we use third-party libraries that may do so for specific purposes. This may include information such as IP address, device model, operating system, and more. The purposes are as follows:
a.
Analytics:
To enhance and optimize our product, we collect analytics data on how the product is used.
b.
Crash Data:
We collect data on app crashes and issues to improve the stability and performance of our app. This information helps us identify and fix potential problems.
c.
Advertisements:
To improve user experience by serving relevant ads.
Users of this Service should be aware that these third parties can access your Personal Information. Their access is for the sole purpose of executing the tasks they are assigned by us. They are strictly prohibited from disclosing or using your information for any purpose other than these tasks.
4. Data Security
We and our partners take every means necessary to protect your data from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of electronic storage is 100% secure and reliable, and we cannot guarantee its absolute security. We continually implement and update administrative, technical, and physical security measures to enhance the protection of your personal information.
5. Third-Party Policies
Our app uses services from third parties, whose privacy practices may differ from ours. Please make sure you read and understand their policies:
Google Analytics Terms of Service
Firebase Data Processing and Security
Firebase Crashlytics
6. Use by Minors
If you reside in the European Union, you must be 16 years of age or older to access and/or use the Services. If you are younger than 16 years old, you must have your legal guardianâ€™s consent and their agreement to this Privacy Policy to access and/or use the Services. In some countries, when the applicable National Law permits, users under 16 may access the Service, provided they are at least 13 years old.
7. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We encourage you to review it regularly to stay informed about our data protection practices.
